s, but show up at every raid and get some nice gear.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'd prefer a variant on your first choice: a group of 3 or 5 people doing the deciding. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukelwinnomad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KelwinNomad</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ebonmoon.com/images/mark.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 3:44 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.ebonmoon.com/images/kd6060.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How would you prefer that your guild assigned loot</span><hr size=1> A combination of 2 and 4 usually works well...   <br>
<br>
Even a group of people could end up favoring certain classes or individuals, but if the group (officers/elders) chose who gets to roll for an item than it is prolly pretty fair...<br>
<br>
The roll itself makes a difference as well.  Everyone rolling 100 makes for an even field, but not if there is a &quot;newer&quot; member rolling with a &quot;veteran&quot;...  I have seen rolling 10x level and thought that to be an extremely fair way of rolling, gives those with more experience a better chance while still leaving it random...<br>
